00:45:06,360 --> 00:45:08,160
Bad taste and terrible design.

715
00:45:08,920 --> 00:45:10,720
Enough with your dark humor.

716
00:45:10,880 --> 00:45:12,440
I'm not joking. I'm being serious.

717
00:45:13,520 --> 00:45:15,240
And why the secrecy?

718
00:45:15,920 --> 00:45:20,200
I'm only finding out now that you bought
a house, decorated and furnished it?

719
00:45:20,400 --> 00:45:22,240
Do I work as a waiter?

720
00:45:22,640 --> 00:45:23,800
No, but it's my business.

721
00:45:24,440 --> 00:45:26,560
I wanted to decorate it myself.
What's the problem?

722
00:45:27,240 --> 00:45:29,400
That's why it's ugly.

723
00:45:29,640 --> 00:45:33,520
I think the house is nice and simple.
It's very you.

724
00:45:33,680 --> 00:45:35,360
Mommy, look.

725
00:45:36,400 --> 00:45:38,200
Rawda's happiness in the pool is enough.

726
00:45:39,400 --> 00:45:42,600
But just so you know, I'll be calling
you every five minutes to check on her.

727
00:45:43,480 --> 00:45:46,520
-It's okay, call every minute if you want.
-Mommy!

728
00:45:47,040 --> 00:45:50,240
See? She doesn't care that I'm
not spending the night with her.

729
00:45:51,480 --> 00:45:53,040
I’m getting a beer. Anyone want one?

730
00:45:53,920 --> 00:45:54,880
I do.

731
00:45:55,320 --> 00:45:57,160
-Me too.
-Okay.

732
00:45:58,760 --> 00:46:00,400
Why can't you be nice?

733
00:46:00,720 --> 00:46:02,120
Can you believe he didn't tell me?

734
00:46:02,880 --> 00:46:06,400
It's normal for him to be confused
and nervous after the divorce.

735
00:46:06,560 --> 00:46:08,840
With you maybe, but why with me?

736
00:46:09,040 --> 00:46:12,520
Rawda hasn't left the country.
She's just spending a day with her dad.

737
00:46:14,040 --> 00:46:14,880
Nadine.

738
00:46:16,400 --> 00:46:18,440
I can't sleep
without my daughter in my arms.

739
00:46:18,840 --> 00:46:20,040
Can I sleep in your arms?

740
00:46:21,120 --> 00:46:22,400
Aren't I your eldest son?

741
00:46:24,920 --> 00:46:26,520
Can I ask you for a favor?

742
00:46:27,480 --> 00:46:28,600
What do you want?

743
00:46:28,800 --> 00:46:31,840
The restaurant people want my photo
for the brochure.

744
00:46:33,560 --> 00:46:36,320
And a journalist who wants to interview me
also needs photos.

745
00:46:37,080 --> 00:46:40,160
So it's up to you; either you take my
photos or I look for someone else.

746
00:46:41,120 --> 00:46:42,480
<i>The strangest woman I've ever met.</i>

747
00:46:42,800 --> 00:46:44,520
I've slept with a lot of women,

748
00:46:45,400 --> 00:46:46,880
but what happened between us

749
00:46:47,200 --> 00:46:49,720
has never happened with anyone
I've been with before.

750
00:46:50,200 --> 00:46:52,920
I didn't understand the theory that
some bodies love each other

751
00:46:53,040 --> 00:46:54,920
at first touch until we were together.

752
00:46:55,520 --> 00:46:57,320
Change your pose.

753
00:46:58,560 --> 00:47:01,880
This is what they call a perfect match,
my dear Nadine.

754
00:47:02,760 --> 00:47:05,920
Every detail was just perfect.

755
00:47:06,440 --> 00:47:08,800
Even after the deed was done.

756
00:47:09,320 --> 00:47:10,560
Don't smile so wide.

757
00:47:11,000 --> 00:47:14,160
Usually I want the one I'm with
to just disappear after.

758
00:47:15,080 --> 00:47:16,360
But that didn't happen with her.

759
00:47:18,280 --> 00:47:19,120
On the contrary,

760
00:47:19,960 --> 00:47:23,120
I'd happily be locked up with her
for a week.

761
00:47:23,600 --> 00:47:26,360
By the way, this is a very important
kind of love.

762
00:47:27,320 --> 00:47:28,160
Love?

763
00:47:29,720 --> 00:47:32,520
You're playing fast and loose
with the word love, don't you think?

764
00:47:33,120 --> 00:47:36,320
Then later you pretend to be a broken
man who's only loved Amira Elini?

765
00:47:37,200 --> 00:47:39,040
What about Mariam? Remember her?

766
00:47:39,440 --> 00:47:42,720
Who's young enough to be your daughter
if you had gotten married after puberty.

767
00:47:43,240 --> 00:47:46,560
Didn't you spend a whole day
teaching your parrot

768
00:47:46,800 --> 00:47:47,920
how to sing for her?

769
00:47:48,320 --> 00:47:51,520
Didn't you think a gesture like that
would get her attached to you?

770
00:47:51,920 --> 00:47:53,040
How are you so selfish?

771
00:47:54,440 --> 00:47:55,680
What about me, Abdallah?

772
00:47:56,200 --> 00:47:58,160
Are you pretending to be a good friend

773
00:47:58,600 --> 00:48:02,320
by distracting me from the fact that for
the first time, my girl is not with me?

774
00:48:04,000 --> 00:48:05,800
Do you only see yourself?

775
00:48:06,400 --> 00:48:07,560
Only think about yourself?

776
00:48:07,880 --> 00:48:09,560
Standing here talking about yourself,

777
00:48:09,960 --> 00:48:12,520
telling me your story
about your new girlfriend.

778
00:48:13,240 --> 00:48:14,920
If you don't mind,

779
00:48:15,120 --> 00:48:16,520
there are other people in the world.

780
00:48:16,600 --> 00:48:18,760
And when they have problems,
like mine for example,

781
00:48:18,960 --> 00:48:22,720
their problems are more important than you
and your different types of love.

782
00:48:23,840 --> 00:48:26,120
-Nadine, I didn't mean to--
-We're done shooting.

783
00:48:28,520 --> 00:48:29,400
Okay.

784
00:48:45,200 --> 00:48:46,120
Here's Mommy.

785
00:48:48,840 --> 00:48:50,240
She didn't want to spend the night.

786
00:48:50,320 --> 00:48:52,920
I'm sorry, Fady. It's her first time.
Do come in, though.

787
00:48:53,080 --> 00:48:55,040
No, I'm going to go. Here's her bag.

788
00:49:02,480 --> 00:49:04,640
Do you know why I didn't have Abdallah
design my house?

789
00:49:07,280 --> 00:49:10,040
So I can have one thing in my life
that doesn't remind me of him.

790
00:49:14,440 --> 00:49:15,400
Goodnight.

791
00:49:19,080 --> 00:49:20,600
<i>Abdallah is not like a brother to me.</i>

792
00:49:21,560 --> 00:49:22,800
<i>He never was.</i>

793
00:49:23,960 --> 00:49:26,200
<i>I've tried to think of him that way</i>
<i>ever since we met,</i>

794
00:49:26,920 --> 00:49:27,880
<i>but I couldn't.</i>

795
00:49:29,160 --> 00:49:30,880
<i>He loved Amira and she loved him.</i>

796
00:49:32,240 --> 00:49:33,400
<i>And Fady loved me.</i>

797
00:49:33,760 --> 00:49:35,120
<i>I thought I could love him back.</i>

798
00:49:36,080 --> 00:49:38,280
<i>He's a thousand times kinder</i>
<i>and nicer than Abdallah.</i>

799
00:49:39,320 --> 00:49:41,240
<i>I tried to hide it from Fady,</i>

800
00:49:42,000 --> 00:49:44,920
<i>but he sensed it, because he's not stupid.</i>

801
00:49:45,560 --> 00:49:47,720
<i>Even though no one loved me</i>
<i>as much as Fady did...</i>

802
00:49:49,280 --> 00:49:50,880
<i>I never wanted to be the reason</i>

803
00:49:51,000 --> 00:49:53,280
<i>that Abdallah and Fady fell out.</i>

804
00:50:06,240 --> 00:50:08,560
Where did you get that Virgin Mary statue?

805
00:50:08,920 --> 00:50:09,760
It was a gift.

806
00:50:10,160 --> 00:50:11,360
A gift.

807
00:50:12,360 --> 00:50:13,360
From a woman, of course.

808
00:50:14,560 --> 00:50:15,960
The one I loved most.

809
00:50:19,640 --> 00:50:23,000
Do you know that I've known we were
going to get here since the day I met you?

810
00:50:25,000 --> 00:50:26,960
I had heard a lot about your cooking.

811
00:50:27,600 --> 00:50:28,720
What did you hear?

812
00:50:29,760 --> 00:50:32,840
I heard it was good, and spicy.

813
00:50:33,760 --> 00:50:35,280
And that when you're in a good mood,

814
00:50:35,600 --> 00:50:37,080
you like to cook for your girlfriends.

815
00:50:38,840 --> 00:50:39,760
What else?

816
00:50:40,160 --> 00:50:41,520
That doesn't matter.

817
00:50:42,480 --> 00:50:44,280
Because what I've seen is much better.

818
00:50:47,600 --> 00:50:49,560
-What kind of pasta?
-Forget the pasta.

819
00:50:51,280 --> 00:50:52,680
Should I prep Madam Abla, Doctor?

820
00:50:53,520 --> 00:50:56,560
-Give me five minutes to have a smoke.
-All right.

821
00:50:59,000 --> 00:51:00,120
This is not good.

822
00:51:00,520 --> 00:51:04,320
I kept thinking about your pasta
while I was in surgery.

823
00:51:04,680 --> 00:51:05,880
Wait till you try the risotto.

824
00:51:07,600 --> 00:51:10,800
I'll start the rice around 2:00 p.m.

825
00:51:11,480 --> 00:51:13,080
Is that a good time for rice?

826
00:51:14,440 --> 00:51:17,600
Yes, today. You have to eat it fresh.

827
00:51:20,040 --> 00:51:21,120
Come in.

828
00:51:22,040 --> 00:51:25,520
-Good morning.
-Good morning... Hey, I have to go.

829
00:51:25,760 --> 00:51:27,120
-Bye.
-How are you?

830
00:51:28,120 --> 00:51:29,800
Hey, Mariam. How are you?

831
00:51:30,080 --> 00:51:32,440
Even though you've been ignoring
me for a while,

832
00:51:32,520 --> 00:51:35,240
not answering my calls or calling me back,

833
00:51:35,320 --> 00:51:36,960
I still thought I'd be the bigger person.

834
00:51:37,480 --> 00:51:40,440
The Farida El Redie project is
keeping me and the company busy.

835
00:51:40,840 --> 00:51:42,520
Not to mention the restaurant opening.

836
00:51:42,720 --> 00:51:45,720
I don't care about any of that.
I'm here to use you.

837
00:51:46,560 --> 00:51:47,400
Oh no.

838
00:51:48,080 --> 00:51:51,240
Daddy got the beach house
we reserved in Ain El Sokhna

839
00:51:51,440 --> 00:51:53,560
and he decided
to start working on it right away.

840
00:51:53,760 --> 00:51:55,320
I told him to leave it to me.

841
00:51:55,600 --> 00:51:57,840
I bet him that I could convince you,

842
00:51:58,560 --> 00:52:01,400
even though you're busy with Farida's
project and your exhibition,

843
00:52:01,560 --> 00:52:03,440
to ditch it all
and work on our beach house.

844
00:52:03,880 --> 00:52:06,600
So that's why you're taking my mother out,

845
00:52:06,760 --> 00:52:08,400
and taking her to all the shopping malls!

846
00:52:08,600 --> 00:52:09,920
You spoil her.

847
00:52:11,000 --> 00:52:12,560
No, there is another reason behind that.

848
00:52:13,240 --> 00:52:14,600
What is it?

849
00:52:15,400 --> 00:52:17,160
Bousa and I are friends. What else?

850
00:52:19,320 --> 00:52:21,280
I don't mind helping you win your bet.

851
00:52:21,520 --> 00:52:22,800
-Really?
-On one condition.

852
00:52:23,320 --> 00:52:25,040
-What?
-Help me make up with Nadine.

853
00:52:26,920 --> 00:52:29,160
INTENSIVE CARE UNIT

854
00:52:31,000 --> 00:52:32,440
<i>Her name is Aida.</i>

855
00:52:32,960 --> 00:52:34,320
<i>She has a son and a daughter.</i>

856
00:52:35,000 --> 00:52:36,520
<i>You will like them.</i>

857
00:52:36,960 --> 00:52:39,160
<i>You will consider her a mother,</i>
<i>and them, siblings.</i>

858
00:52:39,720 --> 00:52:43,000
<i>Impossible. She wouldn't be my mother</i>
<i>even if she was Mother Teresa,</i>

859
00:52:43,400 --> 00:52:44,760
<i>and they'll never be my siblings,</i>

860
00:52:45,000 --> 00:52:46,640
<i>because we don't share the same religion.</i>

861
00:52:47,000 --> 00:52:49,120
<i>Does that mean I'm no longer your father</i>

862
00:52:49,400 --> 00:52:52,360
<i>because we don't share</i>
<i>the same faith anymore?</i>

863
00:52:57,040 --> 00:52:58,080
<i>Sorry if I'm bothering you.</i>

864
00:52:58,640 --> 00:53:00,960
<i>But I wanted to remind you that</i>
<i>I'm always waiting for you.</i>

865
00:53:07,840 --> 00:53:09,200
No perfectionism, please, Nadine.

866
00:53:09,360 --> 00:53:11,600
I want to talk,
and you're the only one who gets me.

867
00:53:11,800 --> 00:53:13,360
I'm a perfectionist, Abdallah?

868
00:53:13,880 --> 00:53:15,800
Do you really think that?

869
00:53:16,680 --> 00:53:18,200
I'm such a devil these days.

870
00:53:18,680 --> 00:53:20,320
Women are all over me right now,

871
00:53:21,000 --> 00:53:23,080
and I feel like I want
to try all of them.

872
00:53:24,080 --> 00:53:26,560
Since you began by admitting
you're a devil,

873
00:53:27,280 --> 00:53:29,000
that you're greedy and horrible,

874
00:53:29,080 --> 00:53:30,680
I think we can come to an agreement.

875
00:53:31,160 --> 00:53:33,240
My "perfect match"
has become an addiction.

876
00:53:34,560 --> 00:53:35,680
I can see her every day,

877
00:53:36,560 --> 00:53:38,440
and every time is like the first time.

878
00:53:40,080 --> 00:53:42,440
Yet when I see the sparkle
in Mariam's eyes,

879
00:53:43,240 --> 00:53:46,800
how she treats Rawda,
and her parents, who remind me of mine,

880
00:53:47,200 --> 00:53:48,800
I think that if I ever do get married,

881
00:53:48,880 --> 00:53:51,160
I won't find a better mother
for my children than her.

882
00:53:51,440 --> 00:53:53,440
Not to mention,

883
00:53:53,720 --> 00:53:55,240
Amira is on my mind all the time.

884
00:53:56,720 --> 00:53:58,080
Follow me to the kitchen.

885
00:53:59,640 --> 00:54:02,520
You only consider Amira to be your
biggest regret, Abdallah,

886
00:54:02,600 --> 00:54:05,440
because it ended with her
before you decided to end it.

887
00:54:06,480 --> 00:54:07,720
Maybe you're right.

888
00:54:08,240 --> 00:54:09,360
And maybe you're wrong.

889
00:54:09,680 --> 00:54:11,480
I'm never wrong.

890
00:54:12,520 --> 00:54:15,080
I never feel good
unless I'm talking to you.

891
00:54:16,080 --> 00:54:19,360
When are you planning on growing up,
you man-baby?

892
00:54:19,960 --> 00:54:22,440
When I find someone that gives me
the peace I find with Mariam,

893
00:54:23,400 --> 00:54:25,680
and the happiness I find with
"Mrs. Perfect,"

894
00:54:26,680 --> 00:54:28,200
and someone to love like I love Amira.

895
00:54:29,240 --> 00:54:32,240
Your late father can send her
down from heaven to you.

896
00:54:32,520 --> 00:54:35,680
Oh, and she has to understand me
like you do.

897
00:54:37,800 --> 00:54:39,800
Shouldn't you call Mariam and Rawda
to come back?

898
00:54:40,040 --> 00:54:41,160
Enough time on the swings.

899
00:54:43,440 --> 00:54:44,400
Thank you.

900
00:54:45,960 --> 00:54:48,640
-What do you mean you don't know?
-I'm confused, Karim.

901
00:54:49,080 --> 00:54:50,960
I feel like I want to see him every day,

902
00:54:51,520 --> 00:54:52,680
I don't get bored of him,

903
00:54:54,680 --> 00:54:56,360
my parents liked him a lot,

904
00:54:56,920 --> 00:54:58,040
he's on my mind a lot.

905
00:54:58,280 --> 00:55:00,280
But that doesn't mean I love him,
of course.

906
00:55:01,840 --> 00:55:03,640
But you do, Mariam.

907
00:55:05,960 --> 00:55:06,800
You love him.

908
00:55:17,680 --> 00:55:20,040
-Something wrong with the car, Ma'am?
-No, Hassan.

909
00:55:20,240 --> 00:55:22,280
-You can go to bed.
-There's no one in the house.

910
00:55:22,360 --> 00:55:24,400
-I know. You can go to bed.
-All right.

911
00:55:34,200 --> 00:55:36,040
Quickly, quickly.

912
00:55:36,320 --> 00:55:37,680
-Give me a kiss.
-You're crazy.

913
00:55:42,560 --> 00:55:44,520
I don't understand myself right now.

914
00:55:45,040 --> 00:55:45,880
Why?

915
00:55:46,240 --> 00:55:49,160
Why? I emptied the entire house

916
00:55:49,600 --> 00:55:50,840
so that you could come.

917
00:55:51,720 --> 00:55:55,040
I let my son travel with his dad
for the first time without me.

918
00:55:56,880 --> 00:56:02,520
Well, you know that I
was smuggled in a car,

919
00:56:03,000 --> 00:56:04,120
like a thief.

920
00:56:06,040 --> 00:56:07,320
Do you know what that means?

921
00:56:09,040 --> 00:56:10,640
I love being crazy with you.

922
00:56:12,720 --> 00:56:13,800
Abdallah.

923
00:56:17,440 --> 00:56:19,400
I'm thinking of a design with this style.

924
00:56:21,240 --> 00:56:23,360
What's this? These are children's rooms.

925
00:56:23,880 --> 00:56:25,960
What can I do? This is how I see you.

926
00:56:26,320 --> 00:56:28,440
I swear to you, I'm not a kid.

927
00:56:28,640 --> 00:56:31,160
People my age have kids already.

928
00:56:31,680 --> 00:56:33,000
It has nothing to do with age.

929
00:56:33,160 --> 00:56:34,520
Even if you were 90 years old,

930
00:56:34,760 --> 00:56:35,840
you'd still be a kid.

931
00:56:36,400 --> 00:56:38,960
-It's a good thing.
-Are you flirting with me?

932
00:56:41,320 --> 00:56:42,320
Are you shy?

933
00:56:47,840 --> 00:56:50,840
Didn't you say your designs depend
on the soul of the clients?

934
00:56:52,120 --> 00:56:54,440
So focus on my soul.

935
00:56:55,160 --> 00:56:56,800
There's more than childhood.

936
00:56:58,320 --> 00:56:59,800
-Really?
-Yeah.

937
00:57:02,440 --> 00:57:04,840
I want to ask you something but I'm
too embarrassed to ask.

938
00:57:05,400 --> 00:57:07,960
I don't allow journalists
to know about my private life.

939
00:57:09,600 --> 00:57:11,480
And what are you hiding?

940
00:57:12,000 --> 00:57:13,400
Shyness or curiosity?

941
00:57:15,920 --> 00:57:17,200
Ask.

942
00:57:17,280 --> 00:57:19,240
I imagine you think of me

943
00:57:19,680 --> 00:57:21,960
as a nice friend or a young girl,

944
00:57:22,480 --> 00:57:23,720
or whatever.

945
00:57:24,920 --> 00:57:26,000
But the question is,

946
00:57:27,320 --> 00:57:29,880
how do you think I see you?

947
00:57:32,280 --> 00:57:33,480
That's a hard question.

948
00:57:37,640 --> 00:57:39,760
Take your time
and think about your answer.

949
00:57:40,960 --> 00:57:42,640
When you find it, call me.

950
00:57:56,280 --> 00:57:57,120
Hello.

951
00:57:58,480 --> 00:57:59,320
What?

952
00:58:06,320 --> 00:58:09,240
<i>If I thought you loved me</i>
<i>just because I was a Christian,</i>

953
00:58:09,760 --> 00:58:11,800
<i>I would have been scared that</i>
<i>you might hate me.</i>

954
00:58:14,720 --> 00:58:19,800
"In the name of Allah the Merciful,
O satisfied soul,

955
00:58:20,160 --> 00:58:23,800
return to your Lord well pleased,
well pleasing.

956
00:58:24,200 --> 00:58:27,960
Join My worshipers and enter My Paradise!"

957
00:58:51,320 --> 00:58:53,880
<i>Islam says "Allah does not</i>
<i>look at your appearance,</i>

958
00:58:53,960 --> 00:58:55,640
<i>He looks at your hearts."</i>

959
00:58:55,840 --> 00:58:58,040
<i>Christianity says "God is love."</i>

960
00:58:58,480 --> 00:59:01,680
<i>In every religion, God tells us</i>
<i>to love with our hearts.</i>

961
00:59:02,680 --> 00:59:03,800
Amira.

962
00:59:07,760 --> 00:59:09,200
Your silence worries me.

963
00:59:13,040 --> 00:59:16,480
I don't know how to thank you for all
you've done since my dad passed.

964
00:59:16,840 --> 00:59:17,800
Thank me?

965
00:59:18,400 --> 00:59:19,640
I thought we were beyond that.

966
00:59:23,600 --> 00:59:24,760
Back in college,

967
00:59:25,600 --> 00:59:27,280
I was in love with a girl.

968
00:59:29,120 --> 00:59:31,440
When we used to ditch classes,
she'd always bring me here.

969
00:59:35,920 --> 00:59:38,360
I can't take any pressure, Abdallah.

970
00:59:39,160 --> 00:59:40,480
I'm not okay.

971
00:59:40,960 --> 00:59:43,160
And I don't want to pressure you, love.

972
01:00:01,520 --> 01:00:03,200
Amira, I'm willing to do anything for you.

973
01:00:03,680 --> 01:00:05,000
I just want to see you happy.

974
01:00:30,240 --> 01:00:32,120
What do you think of this wrapping?

975
01:00:33,400 --> 01:00:34,440
Very impressive.

976
01:00:34,520 --> 01:00:36,360
Seems like we'll be getting
some good news soon.

977
01:00:36,800 --> 01:00:39,520
-Nermin, leave us for a bit.
-Excuse me.

978
01:00:40,960 --> 01:00:42,960
Do you know how long
I've been looking for you?

979
01:00:43,040 --> 01:00:46,200
Fady, consider me on vacation.
I haven't had one for a very long time.

980
01:00:46,320 --> 01:00:48,520
What vacation? We have work to do.

981
01:00:48,640 --> 01:00:49,800
I'm sorry, Fady. Later, later.

982
01:00:50,400 --> 01:00:51,880
I picked out the ring,

983
01:00:52,200 --> 01:00:54,560
asked Nermin to wrap it,

984
01:00:54,720 --> 01:00:55,720
and I went to her.

985
01:00:55,840 --> 01:00:59,200
As soon as I saw her I got too scared,
for fear that I would upset her again.

986
01:01:00,240 --> 01:01:02,000
Mariam asked me about you
a couple of times.

987
01:01:02,760 --> 01:01:04,120
Why aren't you answering her?

988
01:01:06,240 --> 01:01:08,280
Rawda, let's see who can
finish their chocolate first.

989
01:01:08,360 --> 01:01:10,120
Come on. Take it.

990
01:01:10,320 --> 01:01:13,560
Did she really imply something
last time she was in your office?

991
01:01:15,120 --> 01:01:17,040
I finished first.

992
01:01:17,320 --> 01:01:19,040
-Rawda, how could you?
-Abdallah.

993
01:01:19,280 --> 01:01:21,880
When the Amira situation goes south,

994
01:01:22,080 --> 01:01:24,520
you get depressed
and I never know what to do.

995
01:01:25,600 --> 01:01:26,520
Don't worry, Nadine.

996
01:01:26,760 --> 01:01:29,320
You don't know how different
our relationship is now.

997
01:01:30,200 --> 01:01:33,400
It's like the death of her father
has rekindled what we used to have.

998
01:01:33,480 --> 01:01:35,240
She's not in her right mind.

999
01:01:35,520 --> 01:01:38,520
If you had a brain
you would understand that.

1000
01:01:40,160 --> 01:01:41,200
Stop calling me!

1001
01:01:42,720 --> 01:01:45,960
Just twenty thousand.
The girl needs more stuff.

1002
01:01:46,120 --> 01:01:47,320
I'll pay you back.

1003
01:01:47,480 --> 01:01:49,800
Just like I was saying, Eyad, my son.

1004
01:01:49,920 --> 01:01:53,440
The girl goes to work
then comes back so exhausted

1005
01:01:53,560 --> 01:01:56,040
at night from shopping.

1006
01:01:56,240 --> 01:01:59,600
The way you changed the subject when
I came was so cliché.

1007
01:02:00,080 --> 01:02:01,440
Very obvious.

1008
01:02:01,880 --> 01:02:05,400
See? See the way she talks to me,
Mr. Eyad.

1009
01:02:06,760 --> 01:02:10,760
Since she's talking to you like that,
she must've been begging for money.

1010
01:02:11,640 --> 01:02:13,760
She wants ten thousand pounds, right?

1011
01:02:13,920 --> 01:02:15,520
Even though I just gave her twenty.

1012
01:02:15,800 --> 01:02:19,360
But she's not going to leave here
until she makes it thirty.

1013
01:02:19,520 --> 01:02:20,880
I heard twenty.

1014
01:02:21,640 --> 01:02:23,480
-Really?
-Look,

1015
01:02:23,640 --> 01:02:26,520
-I will not allow you to talk to me--
-I don't care!

1016
01:02:26,760 --> 01:02:28,200
Stop being so repulsive.

1017
01:02:58,920 --> 01:03:00,880
I don't like you getting angry
over trivial stuff.

1018
01:03:08,160 --> 01:03:09,440
This is not the first time.

1019
01:03:10,800 --> 01:03:12,280
I threw some money in her face.

1020
01:03:13,480 --> 01:03:14,320
It's over.

1021
01:03:59,240 --> 01:04:00,160
I've missed you.

1022
01:04:00,400 --> 01:04:02,440
Oh! Me too.

1023
01:04:03,960 --> 01:04:06,240
-You look beautiful.
-Look who's talking.

1024
01:04:06,400 --> 01:04:08,120
-How are you, Karim?
-How are you, Nadine?

1025
01:04:08,360 --> 01:04:10,520
I'm good. How's work?

1026
01:04:10,680 --> 01:04:14,040
It's all good. How's your photography?

1027
01:04:14,360 --> 01:04:17,760
Good.
I want you to come check out the photos.

1028
01:04:17,920 --> 01:04:19,760
Yeah, I heard you're having an exhibition.
When?

1029
01:04:19,960 --> 01:04:21,280
Very soon, hopefully.

1030
01:04:21,480 --> 01:04:25,240
Welcome, welcome.
How are you, Mr. Eyad?

1031
01:04:25,720 --> 01:04:27,520
-Welcome, Doctor.
-Thank you, Fady.

1032
01:04:28,000 --> 01:04:30,480
Now I see. All this good work

1033
01:04:30,560 --> 01:04:33,000
is what makes Mr. Architect so cocky.

1034
01:04:33,320 --> 01:04:35,680
Why is he acting like
he hasn't noticed I arrived?

1035
01:04:39,400 --> 01:04:40,960
I'm getting something to drink.

1036
01:04:42,720 --> 01:04:45,800
-Mariam, how are you?
-I'm good, thank you.

1037
01:04:45,960 --> 01:04:47,760
Can I please introduce you to my daughter?

1038
01:04:47,840 --> 01:04:49,080
-Of course.
-This way.

1039
01:04:54,880 --> 01:04:56,680
-What?
-What?

1040
01:04:58,400 --> 01:05:00,800
It's beautiful and amazing.

1041
01:05:03,000 --> 01:05:06,200
Are you going to be a decent person
and say hi to Mr. Eyad and Doctor Farida?

1042
01:05:06,960 --> 01:05:09,640
You delayed their project
and they're there complimenting your work.

1043
01:05:10,520 --> 01:05:11,400
Come on.

1044
01:05:12,400 --> 01:05:13,560
Come with us, Nadine.

1045
01:05:14,320 --> 01:05:15,440
Come on.

1046
01:05:23,440 --> 01:05:25,320
-Mr. Architect.
-Thank you for coming.

1047
01:05:25,600 --> 01:05:26,880
-Thank you.
-Hi, Mr. Architect.

1048
01:05:27,040 --> 01:05:27,880
Hi, Doctor.

1049
01:05:28,200 --> 01:05:29,800
Allow me to introduce Nadine.

1050
01:05:31,120 --> 01:05:33,720
Of course, Mr. Eyad El Wardany
and Dr. Farida Al Redie.

1051
01:05:34,000 --> 01:05:35,160
-Nice to meet you.
-Likewise.

1052
01:05:35,240 --> 01:05:37,400
Great job, your work is like
the Americans or the French.

1053
01:05:37,480 --> 01:05:39,480
-Thank you.
-And I'm assuming it’s over.

1054
01:05:39,600 --> 01:05:41,120
You're done and free to work for us.

1055
01:05:41,240 --> 01:05:42,400
Or not?

1056
01:05:45,160 --> 01:05:46,320
Excuse me.

1057
01:05:47,720 --> 01:05:49,800
-This way, this way.
-Come on.

1058
01:05:55,120 --> 01:05:57,480
Why did you leave me alone, Karim?
I'm nervous.

1059
01:05:58,040 --> 01:05:59,680
He stood there and didn't even say hi.

1060
01:06:03,440 --> 01:06:04,760
I can't believe you came.

1061
01:06:05,200 --> 01:06:06,480
I couldn't not.

1062
01:06:07,160 --> 01:06:09,080
I'm leaving. Bye, Shaimaa.

1063
01:06:09,280 --> 01:06:10,600
-Bye.
-See you soon.

1064
01:06:14,160 --> 01:06:15,880
Can you stop looking at me like that?

1065
01:06:16,400 --> 01:06:17,240
I get shy.

1066
01:06:17,680 --> 01:06:18,880
I can't do that.

1067
01:06:22,640 --> 01:06:24,360
-Congrats, man.
-Thank you, Karim.

1068
01:06:25,400 --> 01:06:26,360
Good evening.

1069
01:06:27,400 --> 01:06:29,360
-Congrats, Abdallah.
-Thank you, Mariam.

1070
01:06:29,560 --> 01:06:31,400
How are you? Excuse me.

1071
01:06:33,400 --> 01:06:34,600
Let me show you around.

1072
01:06:41,880 --> 01:06:46,000
He was so cold. Isn't it enough that
he disappeared after our last talk?

1073
01:06:46,240 --> 01:06:48,000
He knows what I was implying.

1074
01:06:48,080 --> 01:06:49,800
He showed interest more than once.

1075
01:06:49,880 --> 01:06:52,440
But then I showed more interest,
so he's pretending not to notice.

1076
01:06:54,560 --> 01:06:57,280
Why are you upset that he's pretending?
You've been doing it for years.

1077
01:06:57,360 --> 01:06:59,760
Or did you think
I believed you just didn't know?

1078
01:07:02,840 --> 01:07:04,480
I'm a bad actor, it's obvious.

1079
01:07:09,720 --> 01:07:11,760
If you're willing to hurt me this badly,

1080
01:07:14,120 --> 01:07:15,520
that means you're evil, Mariam.

1081
01:07:17,800 --> 01:07:18,920
Very evil.

1082
01:07:34,520 --> 01:07:35,680
Is Rawda okay, Nadine?

1083
01:07:38,240 --> 01:07:40,680
For the first time in my life,
I thought about suicide.

1084
01:07:41,440 --> 01:07:43,480
Your daughter is the only thing
that stopped me.

1085
01:07:45,240 --> 01:07:47,960
-What's wrong, Nadine?
-I'm disgusting, Fady.

1086
01:07:48,240 --> 01:07:51,000
For the first time today,
I realized how disgusting I am.

1087
01:07:53,640 --> 01:07:56,080
I'm alive just to hurt myself
and those who love me.

1088
01:07:56,760 --> 01:07:57,600
You.

1089
01:07:57,800 --> 01:07:59,040
I ruined your life.

1090
01:08:00,080 --> 01:08:02,480
I ruined your relationship
with your friend and your daughter.

1091
01:08:03,640 --> 01:08:08,080
Even right now,
I'm selfishly hurting you with my words.

1092
01:08:09,800 --> 01:08:10,680
Why?

1093
01:08:11,040 --> 01:08:13,280
What do I want? What am I expecting?

1094
01:08:13,440 --> 01:08:15,840
Nothing. Nothing is going to happen.

1095
01:08:23,640 --> 01:08:25,800
Please don't be upset with me, Fady.

1096
01:08:28,520 --> 01:08:31,320
You're good. I'm the terrible one.

1097
01:08:37,080 --> 01:08:39,200
-Don't move.
<i>-You're crazy, Abdallah.</i>

1098
01:08:39,760 --> 01:08:41,760
You're the one who made me crazy.

1099
01:08:42,960 --> 01:08:44,200
<i>Plus, I can really picture you.</i>

1100
01:08:45,760 --> 01:08:46,840
Sitting on a couch,

1101
01:08:47,960 --> 01:08:49,200
<i>bending your knees,</i>

1102
01:08:49,960 --> 01:08:51,280
wearing...

1103
01:08:52,160 --> 01:08:53,240
wearing...

1104
01:08:53,880 --> 01:08:55,200
beige and grey.

1105
01:08:55,800 --> 01:08:57,120
Can you see me or what?

1106
01:08:57,880 --> 01:08:58,720
I had a feeling.

1107
01:08:59,440 --> 01:09:00,520
<i>I said stop moving.</i>

1108
01:09:01,520 --> 01:09:03,160
You can see me!

1109
01:09:05,480 --> 01:09:06,920
Someone's at the door.

1110
01:09:07,320 --> 01:09:09,960
<i>-I'll call you back, okay?</i>
-Okay, bye.

1111
01:09:14,400 --> 01:09:15,760
You were working, right?

1112
01:09:16,840 --> 01:09:18,480
-How are you, Mariouma?
-Hi, Abdallah.

1113
01:09:18,720 --> 01:09:20,600
Mariouma is taking me to the movies today.

1114
01:09:21,920 --> 01:09:24,080
Finish talking to him about your villa.

1115
01:09:24,520 --> 01:09:26,320
Then pick me up downstairs.

1116
01:09:26,440 --> 01:09:27,360
Okay.

1117
01:09:43,240 --> 01:09:45,320
I know you called me a lot
and asked Nadine to--

1118
01:09:45,400 --> 01:09:47,000
Is the answer that difficult?

1119
01:09:49,000 --> 01:09:50,280
You didn't find one?

1120
01:09:50,520 --> 01:09:52,680
Or did you forget altogether?

1121
01:09:53,840 --> 01:09:55,320
I'm still waiting for an answer.

1122
01:09:58,000 --> 01:09:59,360
-Mariouma.
-I'm not Mariouma.

1123
01:09:59,680 --> 01:10:00,920
Mariouma is a little kid.

1124
01:10:01,400 --> 01:10:02,280
I'm not a kid.

1125
01:10:06,760 --> 01:10:08,440
You're the most delicate girl
I've ever met.

1126
01:10:09,720 --> 01:10:12,760
And if I want to be a father,
I won't find a better mother than you.

1127
01:10:14,920 --> 01:10:15,760
But?

1128
01:10:20,160 --> 01:10:22,520
There is always a "but"
after such a nice sentence.

1129
01:10:23,280 --> 01:10:24,520
But what?

1130
01:10:28,160 --> 01:10:29,280
I'll tell you.

1131
01:10:31,280 --> 01:10:34,480
It's obvious that you
don't see me like I see you.

1132
01:10:40,480 --> 01:10:41,600
I have to leave.

1133
01:10:52,080 --> 01:10:55,040
According to my very generous deadlines,

1134
01:10:55,280 --> 01:10:57,760
I was supposed to see the designs
a month ago.

1135
01:10:58,400 --> 01:11:00,760
I know you're not amateurs,
and I don't need to remind you

1136
01:11:00,840 --> 01:11:02,600
that other people's work depends on yours.

1137
01:11:03,840 --> 01:11:06,120
Yes, Doctor, we're not amateurs,

1138
01:11:06,360 --> 01:11:07,480
but the designs--

1139
01:11:07,560 --> 01:11:10,240
Are you the one who's supposed to be
talking about the designs, Fady?

1140
01:11:17,920 --> 01:11:19,880
Here are the designs.
A gift from me to you.

1141
01:11:20,480 --> 01:11:21,800
We'll pay any fine.

1142
01:11:22,440 --> 01:11:25,080
And we won't break any contract
until the doctor makes sure

1143
01:11:25,160 --> 01:11:28,320
that we didn't cause her to lose a pound.

1144
01:11:28,960 --> 01:11:30,520
Wait a minute, please.

1145
01:11:32,400 --> 01:11:35,480
If your time allows, I would like to look
at the designs with you, alone.

1146
01:11:41,320 --> 01:11:44,080
I know I lost my temper. I'm sorry.

1147
01:11:45,080 --> 01:11:46,400
I couldn't control it.

1148
01:11:47,720 --> 01:11:50,120
I've never been afraid to lose anyone
but my son.

1149
01:11:50,800 --> 01:11:51,840
But I'm not your son.

1150
01:11:52,280 --> 01:11:53,200
Or your husband.

1151
01:11:53,640 --> 01:11:54,760
Or even your boyfriend.

1152
01:11:55,680 --> 01:11:57,760
You know what we are
and we can't be anything else.

1153
01:11:58,440 --> 01:12:01,280
I respect this relationship
and that it's a secret.

1154
01:12:02,160 --> 01:12:04,960
But whatever we are, you don't have
the right to talk to me like that

1155
01:12:05,040 --> 01:12:06,920
in front of people.
Or even in your imagination.

1156
01:12:08,680 --> 01:12:10,560
I disappeared, Farida,
because I'm in love.

1157
01:12:11,680 --> 01:12:13,200
And when I'm in love, I don't cheat.

1158
01:12:15,040 --> 01:12:16,560
The one at the opening.

1159
01:12:17,480 --> 01:12:19,080
The one with the cross.

1160
01:12:19,960 --> 01:12:21,920
She's who gave you
the Virgin Mary statue, right?

1161
01:12:22,840 --> 01:12:24,480
Abdallah, I love you, and you love me.

1162
01:12:24,960 --> 01:12:28,080
You know that you won't find what we have
with anyone else.

1163
01:12:29,560 --> 01:12:31,160
I'm sorry, Farida.

1164
01:12:35,000 --> 01:12:36,120
Hi, Mr. Eyad.

1165
01:12:51,200 --> 01:12:53,800
That's Abdallah Younis,
he was dropping off the designs for...

1166
01:13:04,840 --> 01:13:05,800
Let's get married, Amira.

1167
01:13:08,200 --> 01:13:10,520
-That suddenly?
-It's not sudden.

1168
01:13:10,960 --> 01:13:12,680
We've been in love for eleven years.

1169
01:13:13,360 --> 01:13:14,520
Even when we weren't together,

1170
01:13:15,000 --> 01:13:17,440
you couldn't love anyone else
and I couldn't either.

1171
01:13:18,440 --> 01:13:21,520
But the reason we broke up
is still there, Abdallah.

1172
01:13:22,080 --> 01:13:24,480
-It will always be there.
-Don't lie to yourself, Amira.

1173
01:13:24,640 --> 01:13:26,920
There is no reason
that can stop us from loving each other.

1174
01:13:27,400 --> 01:13:28,640
Abdallah.

1175
01:13:29,120 --> 01:13:32,080
You promised to be by my side
without any pressure or commitment.

1176
01:13:32,280 --> 01:13:33,360
I'm not pressuring you,

1177
01:13:34,040 --> 01:13:35,200
but I really do need you.

1178
01:13:35,520 --> 01:13:37,200
And I can't commit this sin.

1179
01:13:38,240 --> 01:13:39,800
-Sin?
-Yes, sin.

1180
01:13:40,000 --> 01:13:41,080
Unforgivable.

1181
01:13:41,760 --> 01:13:44,160
Amira, if you want to keep your religion,
I don't mind.

1182
01:13:44,360 --> 01:13:46,080
This doesn't exist in my religion.

1183
01:13:46,360 --> 01:13:48,520
And I love my religion and I abide by it.

1184
01:13:48,680 --> 01:13:49,720
And I'll always respect it.

1185
01:13:50,880 --> 01:13:53,200
Can you promise not to want kids
if we get married?

1186
01:13:54,280 --> 01:13:56,880
Can you? What about that?

1187
01:13:57,400 --> 01:13:59,440
Could you accept it if our kids
adopted my religion?

1188
01:14:00,520 --> 01:14:03,120
-The Sharia doesn't allow it.
-The Sharia is yours, not mine.

1189
01:14:03,640 --> 01:14:04,920
Your religion is not mine.

1190
01:14:06,280 --> 01:14:07,840
I can't have kids

1191
01:14:08,120 --> 01:14:10,680
and repeat the tragedy I had with my dad.

1192
01:14:11,240 --> 01:14:13,280
It's not true that you're
not pressuring me, Abdallah.

1193
01:14:14,080 --> 01:14:15,480
You're pressuring me greatly.

1194
01:14:16,320 --> 01:14:17,640
And I can't take any more pain.

1195
01:14:18,440 --> 01:14:21,800
It's impossible that God would put this
much love inside us just to torment us.

1196
01:14:22,240 --> 01:14:24,200
Doesn't your religion
say that God is love?

1197
01:14:24,680 --> 01:14:25,920
I'll die without you.

1198
01:14:30,000 --> 01:14:31,280
Amira, I love you very much.

1199
01:14:33,520 --> 01:14:35,920
And I love you more, Abdallah.

1200
01:14:36,240 --> 01:14:38,560
I need you a thousand times more
than you need me.

1201
01:14:39,640 --> 01:14:40,640
Then let's get married.

1202
01:15:02,160 --> 01:15:03,880
<i>I'm a very weak soul.</i>

1203
01:15:06,760 --> 01:15:09,120
<i>I don't feel alive except with him.</i>

1204
01:15:12,680 --> 01:15:14,480
<i>My eyes love looking at him.</i>

1205
01:15:15,920 --> 01:15:17,880
<i>My hands love touching him.</i>

1206
01:15:19,360 --> 01:15:20,600
<i>I love his smell.</i>

1207
01:16:33,600 --> 01:16:35,000
<i>I couldn't, Abdallah.</i>

1208
01:16:36,000 --> 01:16:37,600
<i>I could never have made you happy,</i>

1209
01:16:38,240 --> 01:16:39,600
<i>or been happy with you,</i>

1210
01:16:40,040 --> 01:16:42,560
<i>if I lived with this fear and guilt.</i>

1211
01:16:44,080 --> 01:16:47,120
<i>Don't look for me</i>
<i>because you will never find me.</i>

1212
01:16:50,320 --> 01:16:51,960
What does this mean?

1213
01:16:52,760 --> 01:16:53,600
Huh?

1214
01:16:53,920 --> 01:16:55,080
What does it mean?

1215
01:16:55,320 --> 01:16:58,200
She left this
and didn't say where she was going?

1216
01:16:59,760 --> 01:17:01,160
What? She disappeared?

1217
01:17:02,120 --> 01:17:03,160
Disappeared again?

1218
01:17:05,840 --> 01:17:07,280
She can't disappear!

1219
01:17:09,320 --> 01:17:11,640
Why did she come back
if she was going to do this?

1220
01:17:13,080 --> 01:17:14,400
Yes, so that I go insane!

1221
01:17:17,120 --> 01:17:18,520
It wasn't a dream.

1222
01:17:18,880 --> 01:17:20,040
Didn't you see her with me?

1223
01:17:21,200 --> 01:17:22,280
Didn't you?

1224
01:17:33,360 --> 01:17:36,520
Nadine, you're hiding her inside and
showing her how much I love her, right?

1225
01:17:38,320 --> 01:17:39,200
Right?

1226
01:17:45,680 --> 01:17:47,240
Nadine, I love her so much.

1227
01:17:47,960 --> 01:17:49,720
I don't want anything else in the world.

1228
01:17:54,120 --> 01:17:56,040
I swear, I love her.

1229
01:18:12,680 --> 01:18:15,720
<i>I will not be stubborn</i>
<i>and say that what I did was right,</i>

1230
01:18:16,040 --> 01:18:17,680
<i>because you think it's wrong.</i>

1231
01:18:18,920 --> 01:18:20,400
<i>And because, I swear,</i>

1232
01:18:21,080 --> 01:18:22,800
<i>I don't know what's right</i>
<i>and what's wrong.</i>

1233
01:18:24,200 --> 01:18:26,200
<i>But I can't live unless I'm happy,</i>

1234
01:18:27,320 --> 01:18:30,200
<i>and I would never have been happy</i>
<i>if I didn't do what I did.</i>

1235
01:18:31,600 --> 01:18:32,600
<i>I love you, Amira.</i>

1236
01:18:59,240 --> 01:19:00,400
Do you want me to die?

1237
01:19:01,040 --> 01:19:03,080
Please don't say that, Bousa.

1238
01:19:03,280 --> 01:19:04,760
If I keep seeing you like this,

1239
01:19:05,640 --> 01:19:07,360
I will die from sadness.

1240
01:19:08,560 --> 01:19:09,880
I'm very tired, Mother.

1241
01:19:11,360 --> 01:19:13,040
I'm tired and I don't want to do anything.

1242
01:19:14,840 --> 01:19:16,640
I wish I could hide
inside your belly again.

1243
01:19:17,000 --> 01:19:18,800
In my belly?

1244
01:19:19,480 --> 01:19:20,760
You're a grown man.

1245
01:19:21,200 --> 01:19:23,560
A man. A good man.

1246
01:19:24,240 --> 01:19:26,160
You always get what you want.

1247
01:19:27,840 --> 01:19:31,320
But if you haven't been able
to get her after all these years,

1248
01:19:32,200 --> 01:19:33,600
then she was never yours.

1249
01:19:35,240 --> 01:19:36,560
And she never will be.

1250
01:19:43,200 --> 01:19:45,000
You have the warmest hug, Bousa.

1251
01:19:46,600 --> 01:19:51,680
The hug of a devoted woman has comfort,

1252
01:19:52,120 --> 01:19:53,160
company,

1253
01:19:53,880 --> 01:19:54,760
memories...

1254
01:19:57,920 --> 01:19:59,120
good days...

1255
01:20:01,480 --> 01:20:02,840
and a lot of bad days.

1256
01:20:04,240 --> 01:20:06,880
But the good days make you forget the bad.

1257
01:20:11,160 --> 01:20:14,240
Abdallah, find someone to hug you,

1258
01:20:15,400 --> 01:20:16,920
and then stay there to keep warm.

1259
01:20:25,240 --> 01:20:27,080
-Looks great, Mariouma, congrats.
-Thank you.

1260
01:20:27,200 --> 01:20:28,680
-The house is amazing.
-You like it?

1261
01:20:28,800 --> 01:20:29,640
A lot.

1262
01:20:29,960 --> 01:20:30,920
Thank you.

1263
01:20:35,680 --> 01:20:37,360
I guessed you'd have finished your drink.

1264
01:20:38,200 --> 01:20:39,800
You always come at the right time.

1265
01:20:40,160 --> 01:20:41,280
That's not true.

1266
01:20:42,080 --> 01:20:43,840
Your design is great.

1267
01:20:44,360 --> 01:20:45,200
Thank you.

1268
01:20:45,760 --> 01:20:47,880
-Why are you standing alone?
-We can sit down.

1269
01:20:49,280 --> 01:20:52,240
You must be embarrassed
from all the compliments you get.

1270
01:20:59,840 --> 01:21:01,640
-Can I tell you something?
-Of course.

1271
01:21:02,200 --> 01:21:04,560
I'm sorry about what I said last time.

1272
01:21:05,040 --> 01:21:06,720
I don't know how I said that.

1273
01:21:06,920 --> 01:21:08,560
I shouldn't have said that.

1274
01:21:11,280 --> 01:21:14,320
I shouldn't have blamed you
for something I'm feeling.

1275
01:21:14,400 --> 01:21:15,720
You had nothing to do with it.

1276
01:21:17,200 --> 01:21:18,240
But...

1277
01:21:20,000 --> 01:21:22,360
I couldn't help it.
I couldn't control myself.

1278
01:21:25,240 --> 01:21:27,320
Can I ask your father
for your hand right now?

1279
01:21:30,800 --> 01:21:33,480
-Shady.
-Daddy!

1280
01:21:34,240 --> 01:21:35,200
How are you, sweetie?

1281
01:21:37,600 --> 01:21:39,240
Make sure we're free that day.

1282
01:21:39,960 --> 01:21:41,360
Because we're going to the wedding.

1283
01:21:42,000 --> 01:21:43,080
Come on.

1284
01:22:02,800 --> 01:22:05,240
I can't come to the wedding, Abdallah.

1285
01:22:06,960 --> 01:22:10,040
Rawda has a fever and is vomiting.
I have to take her to the doctor.

1286
01:22:11,160 --> 01:22:13,880
No, Abdallah,
I can't have my mom take her.

1287
01:22:14,200 --> 01:22:16,920
Or Fady.
And don't mention this to him.

1288
01:22:17,000 --> 01:22:19,000
He's been by your side all day.

1289
01:22:19,080 --> 01:22:21,520
Don't ask too much of him.

1290
01:22:24,480 --> 01:22:28,480
I know I have to be with you
on a day like this.

1291
01:22:29,880 --> 01:22:31,000
There's nothing I can do.

1292
01:22:31,240 --> 01:22:34,840
Don't worry. Nadim, the photographer
I sent you, is better than me.

1293
01:22:35,080 --> 01:22:36,360
That's not what I care about.

1294
01:22:36,600 --> 01:22:38,040
I don't need you to take pictures.

1295
01:22:41,360 --> 01:22:42,920
You can't not come.

1296
01:22:43,800 --> 01:22:45,080
Have your mom stay with...

1297
01:22:45,600 --> 01:22:47,640
Hello? Hello?

1298
01:22:55,720 --> 01:22:57,080
We got cut off.

1299
01:23:00,360 --> 01:23:01,800
Why are you so calm?

1300
01:23:02,200 --> 01:23:04,080
Do you know what this means to me?

1301
01:23:07,680 --> 01:23:11,560
She can take her to any hospital,
not necessarily to her doctor at night.

1302
01:23:12,920 --> 01:23:16,000
And why is it a big deal? She gets fevers
then gets better all the time.

1303
01:23:16,080 --> 01:23:17,120
It's not a disaster.

1304
01:23:19,160 --> 01:23:20,600
Why are you so calm?

1305
01:23:21,040 --> 01:23:22,720
Aren't you even worried
about your daughter?

1306
01:23:23,520 --> 01:23:25,320
I'm not, because I know she's okay.

1307
01:23:26,280 --> 01:23:27,520
She's not sick.

1308
01:23:28,440 --> 01:23:29,600
What does that mean?

1309
01:23:38,120 --> 01:23:38,960
Figure it out.

1310
01:23:40,520 --> 01:23:42,120
What would make Nadine,
your best friend,

1311
01:23:42,920 --> 01:23:46,440
the one who gets you the most,
and who you get the most,

1312
01:23:47,400 --> 01:23:48,680
not want to attend your wedding?

1313
01:23:50,720 --> 01:23:52,440
Not want to see you as a groom?

1314
01:23:56,520 --> 01:23:59,240
Did you really never get why Nadine
and I got divorced?

1315
01:24:31,640 --> 01:24:33,440
We're going to have to break up
the company.

1316
01:24:37,720 --> 01:24:38,600
Congrats, Boudy.

1317
01:24:57,480 --> 01:24:59,200
Go on, sweetie. Downstairs.

1318
01:25:04,960 --> 01:25:06,560
Where are you going?

1319
01:25:06,920 --> 01:25:09,200
My son and I are leaving.
We're going back to Zamalek.

1320
01:25:09,880 --> 01:25:12,160
Oh, so you're making
a well thought-out decision.

1321
01:25:12,600 --> 01:25:15,440
And it's final. I can't keep doing this.

1322
01:25:16,000 --> 01:25:17,760
What made you finally make that decision?

1323
01:25:18,800 --> 01:25:20,760
Can't you think of anything?

1324
01:25:20,840 --> 01:25:22,760
Did you really want us
to go to the wedding?

1325
01:25:23,680 --> 01:25:25,080
Was the groom your first or what?

1326
01:25:26,760 --> 01:25:27,800
I loved him.

1327
01:25:28,680 --> 01:25:30,160
Looks like he didn't reciprocate.

1328
01:25:30,640 --> 01:25:32,600
Looks like he just wanted
to sleep with you.

1329
01:25:36,200 --> 01:25:37,080
Divorce me.

1330
01:25:38,240 --> 01:25:39,280
You're divorced, Farida.

1331
01:25:43,840 --> 01:25:46,760
But why Zamalek? Go back to Kitkat.

1332
01:25:47,600 --> 01:25:49,000
<i>I will never go back to Kitkat.</i>

1333
01:25:49,600 --> 01:25:52,000
<i>And I will always be</i>
<i>Doctor Farida Al Redie.</i>

1334
01:25:52,280 --> 01:25:53,160
<i>It's my right.</i>

1335
01:25:53,400 --> 01:25:54,280
<i>I paid for it.</i>

1336
01:25:54,880 --> 01:25:56,320
<i>I upheld my end of the deal.</i>

1337
01:25:57,840 --> 01:25:59,240
<i>But all contracts have to end.</i>

1338
01:25:59,840 --> 01:26:02,000
<i>Mine just ended,</i>
<i>and I'm not renewing it.</i>

1339
01:26:06,720 --> 01:26:09,440
-Use this one.
-Yes, this one.

1340
01:26:09,520 --> 01:26:11,680
-No, put it on this side.
-Can you leave me alone?

1341
01:26:11,760 --> 01:26:13,520
-Fantastic.
-Can you leave me alone?

1342
01:26:15,240 --> 01:26:16,800
-What's wrong?
-All right, excuse us.

1343
01:26:16,880 --> 01:26:18,480
Go in the next room.

1344
01:26:19,320 --> 01:26:20,600
We're sorry.

1345
01:26:21,120 --> 01:26:22,320
You too, Mommy.

1346
01:26:23,440 --> 01:26:24,400
I'm sorry.

1347
01:26:25,040 --> 01:26:26,080
Calm down, dear.

1348
01:26:40,480 --> 01:26:41,600
Why am I scared?

1349
01:26:42,760 --> 01:26:43,760
<i>Isn't this it?</i>

1350
01:26:44,200 --> 01:26:45,960
<i>You were dying to marry Abdallah.</i>

1351
01:26:46,320 --> 01:26:48,880
<i>You're finally doing it.</i>
<i>So why are you so scared?</i>

1352
01:26:52,080 --> 01:26:56,120
<i>I didn't even have time to find out</i>
<i>if Abdallah even loves me.</i>

1353
01:26:58,080 --> 01:27:00,320
<i>Who would I be happy with?</i>

1354
01:27:01,520 --> 01:27:02,760
<i>The one I think I love,</i>

1355
01:27:04,000 --> 01:27:05,640
<i>or the one I'm sure loves me?</i>

1356
01:27:08,280 --> 01:27:09,240
<i>God!</i>

1357
01:28:47,640 --> 01:28:49,840
<i>I can't not be with him</i>
<i>on a day like this.</i>

1358
01:28:51,200 --> 01:28:52,600
<i>I'm his best friend.</i>

1359
01:28:54,600 --> 01:28:56,600
<i>A sister from another mother,</i>
<i>like he says.</i>

1360
01:28:58,200 --> 01:29:00,040
<i>Plus, I'm the reason behind this marriage.</i>

1361
01:29:01,520 --> 01:29:02,800
<i>I can't not be with him.</i>

1362
01:29:06,560 --> 01:29:09,160
Damn it. We can't be late.

1363
01:29:10,960 --> 01:29:12,640
Mommy, it's Boudy.

1364
01:29:20,120 --> 01:29:21,000
I ran away.

1365
01:29:24,880 --> 01:29:26,320
You're crazy, right?

1366
01:29:26,800 --> 01:29:27,880
Have you just noticed?

1367
01:29:28,720 --> 01:29:30,520
Your mother might die.

1368
01:29:33,400 --> 01:29:35,480
She would have
if I was the one who got hurt.

1369
01:29:36,440 --> 01:29:37,280
And Mariam?

1370
01:29:38,880 --> 01:29:40,880
She'll be a lot happier without me.

1371
01:29:47,600 --> 01:29:48,440
I'm lost.

1372
01:29:51,240 --> 01:29:54,320
Well, you've always been lost.

1373
01:29:55,400 --> 01:29:56,240
Get in.

1374
01:29:56,680 --> 01:29:57,680
I'll park first.

1375
01:29:58,400 --> 01:30:01,560
-We were going to the wedding.
-Why are you still awake?

1376
01:30:01,760 --> 01:30:03,320
Kids your age go to bed early.

1377
